node.text: I’m not entirely sure what’s going on but I’m absolutely over the moon. What a week. Thank you so, so much. Staggered by the people I am nominated alongside. Staggered. Thank you @sagawards ❤️

I am truly honoured. Thank you to my friends at the HFPA. This is the stuff that dreams are made of. I’m so proud of the whole Rocketman team, especially @dexfletch . Also congrats to @bernietaupinofficial and @eltonjohn on their song nomination. What a ride. @goldenglobes

Last night I saw The Peanut Butter Falcon. It’s my favourite movie of this year. It’s funny, and moving and full of joy. It’s beautifully acted, looks incredible and it is so well made. Treat yourself. Go and see it. You will not be disappointed.

I dreamed of working at Pixar long before I discovered acting. I’d lie in front of the telly creating my own characters and imagining what it might be like to visit. It is spellbinding. Thank you Terry and Emily for a wonderful afternoon. I will remember it forever. @pixar
@ilmvfx ❤️
So cosy. So smug. 🎄🐻

Last night I went with my family to see The Boy in the Dress @thersc . It is a beautiful, joyous, uplifting, gorgeous new musical based on my friend @dwalliams ‘ book. @guyachambers and @robbiewilliams music is still playing on a loop in my head and I cannot wait to buy the soundtrack. The whole thing is stunning. You absolutely have to go; you’ll laugh, you’ll cry and if you’re anything like me, you’ll immediately want to put on something sequinned and fabulous and score a hat-trick (I definitely would’nt score a hat-trick but I do look amazing in a dress.)

I cannot think of a better way to spend the first week of my 31st year than in this gorgeous place. Thank you @casadecampodr and @godomrep for an incredible week. Stunning scenery and incredible people. Particular thanks to the incredible staff at this beautiful villa for making it a magical experience. I have never experienced luxury like it. The perfect way to celebrate my 30th birthday. Thank you!
I didn’t see that coming! Bloody hell! @recordingacademy #grammys

My best friend recorded my favourite song for my 30th birthday. I love you with all of my heart, Bleddyn. https://youtu.be/V_y4gRQR9Pw

It’s my party and I’ll cry if I want to. I’m the luckiest man alive!

I had lovely time attending @theacademy Governor’s Awards on Sunday. Congratulations to David Lynch, Wes Studi, Geena Davis and the completely amazing Lina Wertmuller. 
Thank you @armani for having my back as always. And thank you to my dear friend @sonialeeartistry for just being you. ❤️ @stevegranitz @gettyentertainment

Chuffed to bits. Me and Roger. The greatest live voice I have ever heard. 
I had amazing night last night watching The Who who were extraordinary. A big highlight was Pete Townshend @yaggerdang telling the Hollywood Bowl to seek me out and feel my bum. That sort of stuff isn’t just in my dreams any more- it actually happens and it’s bloody weird and amazing.

What a week; I saw a life changing performance on Monday. Sang for Joni Mitchell in her living room on Tuesday night with Elton John. And last night performed at the Greek Theatre in Los Angeles with my dear friend for an audience that included Joni (first name terms) and Pete Townshend. I’m not sure what I did in a former life to deserve all of this but I’m loving every minute. I feel truly lucky and hope I never wake up.

Bernie/Elton, Bernie/Elton, Dex.

Tonight I saw @brandicarlile perform Joni Mitchell’s Blue. @eltonjohn and @davidfurnish took me for my birthday. Like many others, I have a deeply profound connection to her music and it makes me feel a great deal when I hear it. I’m not really sure how to convey quite what it is I feel, but I am yet to discover anything else that makes me feel that way. As Brandi said during her show: we don’t live in the age of Shakespeare or Rembrandt. But we do live in the age of Joni.

Tonight I met Joni. She is beautiful. I gave her a gift from Wales. It was one of the best things that has ever happened to me. 
I then saw Brandi perform Blue in it’s entirety with an incredible group of musicians and it was just about the most wonderful thing I have ever seen. I found it very moving and I did not want it to end. My cells are still ringing and vibrating with beautiful words and breathtaking music and a voice that was equal to it. I feel humbled and privileged and profoundly lucky. And a bit like I know myself a little better. 
Brandi, I am in awe of You. And Joni. And Blue.
Found my friends in the City of Angels❤️ @davidfurnish @eltonjohn
